Key Match Events: England clinched its ticket to the Euro 2024 semifinals in dramatic fashion on Saturday, advancing on penalty kicks against Switzerland.
Bukayo Saka scored the equalizer on a strike from outside the box in the 80th minute to help send the match to extra time.
Post-Match Reflections: England will take on the winner of Saturday's Netherlands-Turkey match on Wednesday as it seeks to make the final of the tournament for the second straight time.
Miscellaneous Highlights: This marks the second straight match that England will play in extra time, getting a goal a few minutes into the bonus 30 minutes in its Round of 16 win over Slovenia.
